acceptOwnership().details: Allows an ownership transfer to be completed by the recipient.

params._added: is the list of addresses for the new Oracles being added

params._maxSubmissions: is the new maximum submission count for each round
params._minSubmissions: is the new minimum submission count for each round
params._removed: is the list of addresses for the new Oracles being removed
params._restartDelay: is the number of rounds an Oracle has to wait before they can initiate a round

params._decimals: represents the number of decimals to offset the answer by
params._description: a short description of what is being reported
params._link: The address of the LINK token
params._maxSubmissionValue: is an immutable check for an upper bound of what submission values are accepted from an oracle
params._minSubmissionValue: is an immutable check for a lower bound of what submission values are accepted from an oracle
params._paymentAmount: The amount paid of LINK paid to each oracle per submission, in wei (units of 10⁻¹⁸ LINK)
params._timeout: is the number of seconds after the previous round that are allowed to lapse before allowing an oracle to skip an unfinished round
params._validator: is an optional contract address for validating external validation of answers

params._oracle: is the address of the oracle whose admin is being queried

userdoc.notice: Handles aggregating data pushed in from off-chain, and unlocks payment for oracles as they report. Oracles' submissions are gathered in rounds, with each round aggregating the submissions for each oracle into a single answer. The latest aggregated answer is exposed as well as historical answers and their updated at timestamp.
